    <title>Arcade Fire released an epic 45-minute single — in Headspace’s meditation app</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="2018 Life Is Beautiful Festival - Day 3" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/UT8NRn0mD5SlQLaPw6TWaoPBMAc=/0x39:3000x2039/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/69132982/1039320710.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Photo by Tim Mosenfelder/Getty Images&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="pdwbRQ"&gt;Arcade Fire has a new single out — sort of. The Canadian indie rock band has released a new 45-minute instrumental composition called “Memories In The Age Of Anxiety,” but the new song is actually a collaboration with meditation app Headspace, and you can only listen to it there.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="QCudSP"&gt;The new track was created in collaboration with John Legend and, as &lt;a href="https://www.stereogum.com/2144197/arcade-fire-release-new-45-minute-song-for-meditation-app/music/"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Stereogum&lt;/em&gt; notes&lt;/a&gt;, is one of the first new pieces of music from the group since its cover of “&lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qpYOstfcQBs"&gt;Baby Mine&lt;/a&gt;” in the 2019 live-action version of &lt;em&gt;Dumbo.&lt;/em&gt; (It’s the band’s first original song since its 2017 studio album &lt;em&gt;Everything Now.&lt;/em&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
